### 3. complete_task (Unchanged)

#### Description
Mark a task as completed.

#### Input Parameters
```json
{
  "user_id": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": true,
    "description": "User identifier (must match authenticated user)",
    "validation": {
      "min_length": 1,
      "max_length": 255
    }
  },
  "task_id": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": true,
    "description": "Unique identifier of the task to complete",
    "validation": {
      "min_length": 1,
      "max_length": 255
    }
  }
}
```

#### Output Response
```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "task_id": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier of the completed task"
    },
    "completed": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "description": "Boolean indicating the task is now completed"
    },
    "updated_at": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "Timestamp when the task was updated to completed status"
    }
  },
  "required": ["task_id", "completed", "updated_at"]
}
```

#### Error Responses
- `400 Bad Request`: Invalid input parameters
- `401 Unauthorized`: Invalid user_id or task doesn't belong to user
- `404 Not Found`: Task not found
- `500 Internal Server Error`: Database operation failed

