### 4. update_task (Enhanced)

#### Description
Update the title, description, priority, or tags of an existing task.

#### Input Parameters
```json
{
  "user_id": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": true,
    "description": "User identifier (must match authenticated user)",
    "validation": {
      "min_length": 1,
      "max_length": 255
    }
  },
  "task_id": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": true,
    "description": "Unique identifier of the task to update",
    "validation": {
      "min_length": 1,
      "max_length": 255
    }
  },
  "title": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": false,
    "description": "New task title (optional - only if changing title)",
    "validation": {
      "min_length": 1,
      "max_length": 200
    }
  },
  "description": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": false,
    "description": "New task description (optional - only if changing description, null to clear)",
    "validation": {
      "max_length": 2000
    }
  },
  "priority": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": false,
    "description": "New priority level for the task",
    "enum": ["high", "medium", "low"],
    "validation": {
      "enum_values": ["high", "medium", "low"]
    }
  },
  "tags": {
    "type": "array",
    "items": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "required": false,
    "description": "New array of tags for the task (completely replaces existing tags)",
    "validation": {
      "max_items": 10,
      "item_min_length": 1,
      "item_max_length": 50,
      "pattern": "^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$"
    }
  }
}
```

#### Output Response
```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "task_id": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier of the updated task"
    },
    "updated_fields": {
      "type": "object",
      "description": "Object containing the fields that were updated",
      "properties": {
        "title": {"type": "string"},
        "description": {"type": "string"},
        "priority": {"type": "string"},
        "tags": {
          "type": "array",
          "items": {"type": "string"}
        },
        "updated_at": {
          "type": "string",
          "format": "date-time"
        }
      }
    },
    "updated_at": {
      "type": "string",
      "format": "date-time",
      "description": "Timestamp when the task was last updated"
    }
  },
  "required": ["task_id", "updated_fields", "updated_at"]
}
```

#### Error Responses
- `400 Bad Request`: Invalid input parameters or no fields provided for update
- `401 Unauthorized`: Invalid user_id or task doesn't belong to user
- `404 Not Found`: Task not found
- `500 Internal Server Error`: Database operation failed

---

### 5. delete_task (Unchanged)

#### Description
Permanently delete a task.

#### Input Parameters
```json
{
  "user_id": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": true,
    "description": "User identifier (must match authenticated user)",
    "validation": {
      "min_length": 1,
      "max_length": 255
    }
  },
  "task_id": {
    "type": "string",
    "required": true,
    "description": "Unique identifier of the task to delete",
    "validation": {
      "min_length": 1,
      "max_length": 255
    }
  }
}
```

#### Output Response
```json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "success": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "description": "Indicates whether the deletion was successful"
    },
    "task_id": {
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Unique identifier of the deleted task"
    }
  },
  "required": ["success", "task_id"]
}
```

#### Error Responses
- `400 Bad Request`: Invalid input parameters
- `401 Unauthorized`: Invalid user_id or task doesn't belong to user
- `404 Not Found`: Task not found
- `500 Internal Server Error`: Database operation failed

## Backward Compatibility

All existing functionality is preserved:
- All original MCP tools remain available with their original signatures
- New optional parameters have sensible defaults
- Existing clients will continue to work without modification
- Response formats maintain backward compatibility

## Performance Requirements

- `add_task`: Response time < 100ms
- `list_tasks`: Response time < 2s for searches up to 1000 tasks
- `complete_task`: Response time < 100ms
- `update_task`: Response time < 100ms
- `delete_task`: Response time < 100ms

## Security Requirements

- User isolation: Users can only access/modify their own tasks
- Input validation: All parameters validated before processing
- SQL injection prevention: All queries use parameterized statements
- Rate limiting: Appropriate rate limits to prevent abuse